<hr />
<h3 id="whentochoosewhich"><strong>When to Choose Which?</strong></h3>
<pre><code>┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                 DECISION GUIDE                           │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

CHOOSE GITHUB IF:
─────────────────
✅ Building open source projects
✅ Want largest developer community
✅ Portfolio/personal projects
✅ Need extensive marketplace (Actions)
✅ Prefer simplicity
✅ Social coding (stars, followers)
✅ Using GitHub Pages for blog/portfolio
✅ Learning Git (easier interface)

Examples:
├─ Personal portfolio
├─ Open source library
├─ Student projects
├─ Community-driven projects
└─ Resume building


CHOOSE GITLAB IF:
─────────────────
✅ Need self-hosted solution
✅ Enterprise DevOps requirements
✅ Complete CI/CD out-of-the-box
✅ Advanced project management
✅ Data sovereignty concerns
✅ Integrated security scanning
✅ Need unlimited CI/CD minutes
✅ Want single application for DevOps

Examples:
├─ Enterprise applications
├─ Government projects
├─ Regulated industries
├─ Companies with own infrastructure
└─ Complete DevOps pipeline needs


BOTH ARE GREAT FOR:
───────────────────
✅ Version control
✅ Collaboration
✅ Code review
✅ Issue tracking
✅ Git workflows
✅ Team projects
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h3 id="migrationbetweenplatforms"><strong>Migration Between Platforms</strong></h3>
<pre><code class="bash language-bash"># Migrate from GitHub to GitLab
# (and vice versa)

OPTION 1: Import Project
────────────────────────
1. GitLab → New Project → Import Project
2. Choose "GitHub"
3. Authenticate with GitHub
4. Select repositories to import
5. Click "Import"

Imports:
├─ Repository and branches
├─ Issues
├─ Pull/Merge requests
├─ Wiki
└─ Milestones


OPTION 2: Manual Migration
──────────────────────────
# Clone from GitHub
git clone https://github.com/user/repo.git
cd repo

# Add GitLab as new remote
git remote add gitlab https://gitlab.com/user/repo.git

# Push all branches
git push gitlab --all

# Push all tags
git push gitlab --tags


OPTION 3: Mirror Repository
────────────────────────────
# Keep both in sync
GitLab → Settings → Repository → Mirroring repositories
Pull/Push from GitHub
</code></pre>
