<h2 id="2gitlabcevsgitlabee">2️⃣ GitLab CE vs GitLab EE</h2>
<h3 id="whatareceandee"><strong>What are CE and EE?</strong></h3>
<p><strong>Definitions</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>GitLab CE (Community Edition)</strong>: Free, open-source version with core features</li>
<li><strong>GitLab EE (Enterprise Edition)</strong>: Paid version with advanced features for enterprises</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="simpleanalogy-1"><strong>Simple Analogy</strong> 🏪</h3>
<pre><code>GitLab Editions = Software Tiers

Community Edition (CE):
├─ Like free version of software
├─ Core features included
├─ Perfect for small teams
└─ Open source

Enterprise Edition (EE):
├─ Like premium version
├─ All CE features + advanced tools
├─ For large organizations
└─ Paid tiers
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h3 id="detailedcomparison-1"><strong>Detailed Comparison</strong></h3>
<pre><code>┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│           GITLAB CE vs EE COMPARISON                        │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

