<pre><code class="bash language-bash"># ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# MERGING LOCALLY (Not Recommended for Teams)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# 1. Ensure main is up-to-date
$ git checkout main
$ git pull origin main

# 2. Merge feature branch
$ git merge feature/add-dashboard

Merge made by the 'recursive' strategy.
 dashboard.html | 45 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 45 insertions(+)

# 3. Push merged result
$ git push origin main

# 4. Delete feature branch
$ git branch -d feature/add-dashboard
$ git push origin --delete feature/add-dashboard

⚠️ Warning: This bypasses code review!
          Use Merge Requests instead for team projects.
</code></pre>
