<h2 id="6visualstudiocodeinstallation">6️⃣ Visual Studio Code Installation</h2>
<h3 id="whatisvscode"><strong>What is VS Code?</strong></h3>
<p><strong>Definition</strong>: 
<strong>Visual Studio Code (VS Code)</strong> is a free, open-source code editor developed by Microsoft. It's lightweight yet powerful, with extensive extension support.</p>
<h3 id="whyvscode"><strong>Why VS Code?</strong></h3>
<pre><code>✅ Free &amp; open source
✅ Lightweight (fast startup)
✅ Cross-platform (Windows, Mac, Linux)
✅ Huge extension marketplace
✅ Built-in Git support
✅ Integrated terminal
✅ IntelliSense (autocomplete)
✅ Debugging support
✅ Active development
✅ Large community
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h3 id="installationsteps"><strong>Installation Steps</strong></h3>
<h4 id="windows"><strong>🪟 Windows</strong></h4>
<pre><code>METHOD 1: Download from Website
────────────────────────────────

1. Visit: https://code.visualstudio.com/

2. Click [Download for Windows]
   (Downloads: VSCodeUserSetup-x64-1.85.0.exe)

3. Run installer

   ┌────────────────────────────────────────┐
   │ Visual Studio Code Setup               │
   ├────────────────────────────────────────┤
   │                                        │
   │ Select Additional Tasks:               │
   │                                        │
   │ ☑ Add "Open with Code" to context    │
   │   menu (right-click option)            │
   │ ☑ Add to PATH                         │
   │ ☑ Register Code as editor for         │
   │   supported file types                 │
   │ ☑ Create desktop icon                 │
   │                                        │
   │ [Install]                              │
   └────────────────────────────────────────┘

4. Click Install

5. Launch VS Code ✓


METHOD 2: Using Winget
──────────────────────

# Open PowerShell/Command Prompt
winget install Microsoft.VisualStudioCode


METHOD 3: Using Chocolatey
───────────────────────────

# Open PowerShell as Administrator
choco install vscode -y
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h4 id="macos"><strong>🍎 macOS</strong></h4>
<pre><code>METHOD 1: Download from Website
────────────────────────────────

1. Visit: https://code.visualstudio.com/

2. Click [Download for Mac]
   (Downloads: VSCode-darwin-universal.zip)

3. Open downloaded .zip file

4. Drag "Visual Studio Code.app" to Applications folder

5. Open from Applications or Spotlight (⌘ + Space, type "code")


METHOD 2: Using Homebrew
─────────────────────────

# Install Homebrew first (if not installed)
/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"

# Install VS Code
brew install --cask visual-studio-code


COMMAND LINE INTEGRATION:
─────────────────────────

1. Open VS Code
2. ⌘ + Shift + P (Command Palette)
3. Type: "shell command"
4. Click "Shell Command: Install 'code' command in PATH"

Now you can open files/folders from terminal:
$ code myfile.js
$ code .  (open current directory)
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h4 id="linuxubuntudebian"><strong>🐧 Linux (Ubuntu/Debian)</strong></h4>
<pre><code>METHOD 1: Via Snap (Easiest)
─────────────────────────────

sudo snap install --classic code


METHOD 2: Via APT Repository
─────────────────────────────

# Update package index and install dependencies
sudo apt update
sudo apt install software-properties-common apt-transport-https wget -y

# Import Microsoft GPG key
wget -qO- https://packages.microsoft.com/keys/microsoft.asc | gpg --dearmor &gt; packages.microsoft.gpg
sudo install -o root -g root -m 644 packages.microsoft.gpg /etc/apt/trusted.gpg.d/

# Add VS Code repository
sudo sh -c 'echo "deb [arch=amd64] https://packages.microsoft.com/repos/vscode stable main" &gt; /etc/apt/sources.list.d/vscode.list'

# Install VS Code
sudo apt update
sudo apt install code -y


METHOD 3: Download .deb Package
────────────────────────────────

1. Visit: https://code.visualstudio.com/

2. Click [.deb] download

3. Install:
sudo dpkg -i code_*.deb
sudo apt-get install -f  # Fix dependencies


LAUNCH:
───────
code
# or from applications menu
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h3 id="firstlaunchsetup"><strong>First Launch Setup</strong></h3>
<pre><code>WHEN YOU FIRST OPEN VS CODE:
─────────────────────────────

1. Welcome Screen
   ┌────────────────────────────────────────┐
   │ Welcome to Visual Studio Code          │
   ├────────────────────────────────────────┤
   │                                        │
