<h2 id="7autogitinvscode">7️⃣ Auto Git in VS Code</h2>
<h3 id="whatisautogit"><strong>What is Auto Git?</strong></h3>
<p><strong>Definition</strong>: 
<strong>Auto Git</strong> refers to VS Code's built-in Git integration and extensions that automate Git operations, providing visual Git management without using command line.</p>
<hr />
<h3 id="vscodebuiltingitfeatures"><strong>VS Code Built-in Git Features</strong></h3>
<pre><code>┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│          VS CODE GIT FEATURES                            │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

INCLUDED BY DEFAULT:
────────────────────
✅ Visual diff viewer
✅ Stage/unstage files
✅ Commit with GUI
✅ Branch management
✅ Push/pull
✅ Conflict resolution
✅ Git blame
✅ Timeline view
✅ Merge conflict helper
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h3 id="sourcecontrolpanel"><strong>Source Control Panel</strong></h3>
<pre><code>Click Source Control icon (Ctrl/⌘ + Shift + G)

┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ SOURCE CONTROL                           ⚙️     │
├────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                │
│ Message                                        │
│ ┌────────────────────────────────────────┐   │
│ │ Add login feature                       │   │
│ └────────────────────────────────────────┘   │
│ [✓ Commit] [∼ Sync Changes ▼]                │
│                                                │
│ CHANGES (3)                                    │
│ ├─ M src/login.js                     [+][-]  │
│ ├─ A src/auth.js                      [+]     │
│ └─ D old-code.js                      [-]     │
│                                                │
│ STAGED CHANGES (1)                             │
│ └─ M README.md                        [-]     │
│                                                │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

Symbols:
M = Modified
A = Added (new file)
D = Deleted
U = Untracked
C = Conflict

Actions:
[+] = Stage
[-] = Unstage
[↻] = Discard changes
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h3 id="gitworkflowinvscode"><strong>Git Workflow in VS Code</strong></h3>
<h4 id="step1initializerepository"><strong>Step 1: Initialize Repository</strong></h4>
<pre><code>METHOD 1: From Source Control Panel
────────────────────────────────────
1. Open folder: File → Open Folder
2. Click Source Control icon
3. Click [Initialize Repository]
4. Git initialized! ✓


METHOD 2: From Command Palette
───────────────────────────────
1. Ctrl/⌘ + Shift + P
2. Type: "Git: Initialize Repository"
3. Select folder
4. Done! ✓
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h4 id="step2stagefiles"><strong>Step 2: Stage Files</strong></h4>
<pre><code>STAGE INDIVIDUAL FILES:
───────────────────────
├─ Hover over file in CHANGES
└─ Click [+] to stage

STAGE ALL FILES:
────────────────
Click [+] next to "CHANGES"

STAGE SELECTED LINES:
─────────────────────
1. Open file
2. Select lines
3. Right-click
4. "Stage Selected Ranges"
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h4 id="step3commit"><strong>Step 3: Commit</strong></h4>
<pre><code>1. Type commit message in text box

   ┌────────────────────────────────────────┐
   │ Add user authentication                │
   │                                        │
   │ - Implement login form                 │
   │ - Add JWT token handling               │
   │ - Create auth middleware               │
   └────────────────────────────────────────┘

2. Click [✓ Commit]

OR

Ctrl/⌘ + Enter (commit)

AMEND LAST COMMIT:
──────────────────
Click [...] → Commit → Commit (Amend)
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h4 id="step4viewhistory"><strong>Step 4: View History</strong></h4>
<pre><code>TIMELINE VIEW:
──────────────
1. Select file in Explorer
2. View Timeline panel (bottom of Explorer)
3. See all commits affecting this file

GIT GRAPH EXTENSION:
────────────────────
Install "Git Graph" extension
Click "Git Graph" in status bar
Visual commit history!

┌────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  * a1b2c3d  Add login     (main)       │
│  │                                     │
│  * b2c3d4e  Fix header                 │
│  │                                     │
│  *───┐                                 │
│  │   * c3d4e5f  Add footer (feature)  │
│  │   │                                 │
│  │   * d4e5f6g  Style changes          │
│  │   │                                 │
│  * ──┘ e5f6g7h  Merge feature          │
│  │                                     │
│  * f6g7h8i  Initial commit             │
└────────────────────────────────────────┘
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h4 id="step5branching"><strong>Step 5: Branching</strong></h4>
<pre><code>CREATE BRANCH:
──────────────
1. Click branch name in status bar (bottom-left)
2. "Create new branch from..."
3. Enter name: "feature/dark-mode"
4. Branch created and switched! ✓

OR

Command Palette → "Git: Create Branch"


SWITCH BRANCHES:
────────────────
1. Click branch name in status bar
2. Select branch from list

OR

Ctrl/⌘ + Shift + P → "Git: Checkout to..."


DELETE BRANCH:
──────────────
Command Palette → "Git: Delete Branch"
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h4 id="step6pushpull"><strong>Step 6: Push/Pull</strong></h4>
<pre><code>PUSH:
─────
Method 1: Click [↑] in Source Control
Method 2: Status bar cloud icon
Method 3: [...] → Push

PULL:
─────
Method 1: Click [↓] in Source Control
Method 2: [...] → Pull

SYNC (Pull + Push):
───────────────────
Click [∼ Sync Changes] button
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h3 id="gitlensextensionsuperchargedgit"><strong>GitLens Extension</strong> (Supercharged Git)</h3>
<pre><code>INSTALL GITLENS:
────────────────
1. Extensions (Ctrl/⌘ + Shift + X)
2. Search "GitLens"
3. Install by GitKraken

FEATURES:
─────────

1. INLINE BLAME
   Shows author &amp; date at end of each line

   function login() {  // John Doe, 2 days ago
     ...
   }

2. FILE HISTORY
   Complete file commit history

3. LINE HISTORY
   See who changed specific line

4. CURRENT LINE BLAME
   Hover over line → see full commit details

5. CODELENS
   Shows "Recent change" above functions

   // Recent change: John Doe, 2 days ago | 5 authors
   function authenticate() {
     ...
   }

6. SIDE-BY-SIDE COMPARISON
   Compare current vs previous versions

7. REPOSITORY VIEW
   Visual repository structure with commits
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h3 id="autogitextension"><strong>Auto Git Extension</strong></h3>
<pre><code>INSTALL AUTO GIT:
─────────────────
Extensions → Search "Auto Git" → Install

FEATURES:
─────────
├─ Auto-fetch (pulls changes periodically)
├─ Auto-commit (commits on file save)
├─ Auto-push (pushes after commit)
└─ Configurable intervals

SETTINGS:
─────────
File → Preferences → Settings
Search "Auto Git"

┌────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Auto Git Configuration                 │
├────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ ☑ Auto Fetch                          │
│   Interval: [60] seconds              │
│                                        │
│ ☐ Auto Commit                         │
│   Message: "Auto commit"              │
│                                        │
│ ☐ Auto Push                           │
│   After each commit                   │
└────────────────────────────────────────┘

⚠️ USE WITH CAUTION:
Auto-commit can create messy history
Better for personal projects only
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h3 id="conflictresolutioninvscode"><strong>Conflict Resolution in VS Code</strong></h3>
<pre><code>WHEN CONFLICT OCCURS:
─────────────────────

1. VS Code highlights conflicts

   ┌────────────────────────────────────────┐
   │ config.js                        [×]   │
   ├────────────────────────────────────────┤
   │                                        │
   │ const express = require('express');    │
   │ &lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt; Current Change                 │
   │ const PORT = 8080;                     │
   │ [Accept Current Change]                │
   │ [Accept Both Changes]                  │
   │ [Compare Changes]                      │
   │ =======                                │
   │ const PORT = 5000;                     │
   │ [Accept Incoming Change]               │
   │ &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Incoming Change                │
   │                                        │
   └────────────────────────────────────────┘


2. CLICK BUTTONS:
   ├─ Accept Current Change (keep your version)
   ├─ Accept Incoming Change (keep their version)
   ├─ Accept Both Changes (keep both)
   └─ Compare Changes (side-by-side view)


3. OR EDIT MANUALLY:
   Delete conflict markers
   Keep desired code


4. MARK AS RESOLVED:
   Source Control → Stage file (+)


5. COMMIT:
   Message: "Resolve merge conflict in config.js"
   Click Commit
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h3 id="essentialgitextensionsforvscode"><strong>Essential Git Extensions for VS Code</strong></h3>
<pre><code>┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│         RECOMMENDED GIT EXTENSIONS                       │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

1. GITLENS ⭐ (Must-have)
   ├─ Supercharged Git capabilities
   ├─ Blame annotations
   ├─ File history
   └─ Author: GitKraken

2. GIT GRAPH
   ├─ Visual commit graph
   ├─ Branch visualization
   └─ Author: mhutchie

3. GIT HISTORY
   ├─ View git log
   ├─ Compare branches
   └─ Author: Don Jayamanne

4. GITIGNORE
   ├─ Language-specific .gitignore templates
   └─ Author: CodeZombie

5. GIT BLAME
   ├─ See Git Blame information
   └─ Author: Wade Anderson

6. MERGE CONFLICT
   ├─ Better conflict visualization
   └─ Author: Shane Carvalho


INSTALL ALL AT ONCE:
────────────────────
Ctrl/⌘ + Shift + P
"Extensions: Show Recommended Extensions"
Install Workspace Recommendations
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h3 id="gitinintegratedterminal"><strong>Git in Integrated Terminal</strong></h3>
<pre><code>VS Code terminal has Git commands:

# Open Terminal: Ctrl/⌘ + `

$ git status
On branch main
Your branch is up to date with 'origin/main'.

$ git log --oneline
a1b2c3d (HEAD -&gt; main) Latest commit
b2c3d4e Previous commit

$ git diff

# All Git commands work!

SPLIT TERMINALS:
────────────────
Click [+] icon in terminal
Run different commands simultaneously

Terminal 1: npm start
Terminal 2: git status
Terminal 3: npm test
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h2 id="8bestpracticessummary">8️⃣ Best Practices Summary</h2>
<h3 id="gitlabbestpractices"><strong>GitLab Best Practices</strong></h3>
<pre><code>✅ DO:
──────
1. Use Merge Requests for all changes
2. Write descriptive MR descriptions
3. Add reviewers before merging
4. Use CI/CD pipelines
5. Tag releases
6. Use issue boards for project management
7. Document in wikis
8. Use protected branches
9. Enable merge checks
10. Regular backups (if self-hosted)

❌ DON'T:
──────────
1. Push directly to main/master
2. Merge without review
3. Ignore failing pipelines
4. Commit sensitive data
5. Leave stale branches
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h3 id="vscodebestpractices"><strong>VS Code Best Practices</strong></h3>
<pre><code>✅ DO:
──────
1. Use extensions wisely (not too many)
2. Learn keyboard shortcuts
3. Use workspace settings for projects
4. Sync settings across machines
5. Use integrated terminal
6. Leverage IntelliSense
7. Format code (Shift + Alt + F)
8. Use debugging tools
9. Customize for your workflow
10. Keep VS Code updated

❌ DON'T:
──────────
1. Install every extension you see
2. Ignore performance warnings
3. Work without Git integration
4. Skip learning shortcuts
5. Use default settings blindly
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h2 id="quickreferencecard">🎯 Quick Reference Card</h2>
<pre><code class="bash language-bash"># ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# GITLAB COMMANDS
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Clone GitLab repo
git clone https://gitlab.com/username/project.git

# Add GitLab remote
git remote add gitlab https://gitlab.com/username/project.git

# Push to GitLab
git push gitlab main

# Create MR (via web UI)
Visit GitLab → Create Merge Request


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
